Titolo: Aperture Tag

Anno: 2014

Descrizione: Aperture Tag: The Paint Gun Testing Initiative is a 2014 first-person puzzle-platform video game developed by the Aperture Tag Team. Originally made as a mod of Valve's Portal series, it was released on July 15, 2014. The game removes the iconic portal gun of the series and instead utilizes a newly created paint gun that fires two kinds of gel with different properties. The game features new characters and voice acting, along with a co-op mode that includes a level editor.

